content.detailedDescription: I submitted a report a few days ago involving orb sightings in nassau county ny that i observed on october 12, 2016.  today driving on the meadowbrook parkway north i saw a white orb so i took a picture.  then throughout the day, i took other pictures in different locations at various times.  my pictures include sightings form the meadowbrook parkway north and south, loop parkway and lido blvd.  my personal observations only revealed 1 or 2 orbs.  my pictures however showed a lot more detail such as multiple orbs blue and white, a white triangle, a white curved line and a purple rectangle.  as observed in my prior posting, a large orb was directly above the sun and smaller ones scattered. i wanted to make sure my phone camera was taking accurate photos so i called a friend approximately 18 miles from where i was and asked her to take some pictures of the sun.  like mine, her pictures showed a large orb directly over the sun and smaller ones scattered, however the large orb in her photos had a purple light surrounding the large white orb.  i suspect that these orbs around the sun have been hanging out in that location on a daily bases for some time.  i think it would be a great idea for everyone reading this post to take some pictures of the sun and if any orbs or other objects are observed to post them on this site. my last attached photo is the one my friend took with her phone camera.  try to expand the photos when viewing to see the details better.  i apologize if some of my photos are redundant but i am new at locating and posting photos.

content.detailedDescription:
About 5 weeks ago while walking our dog, we were noticing a bright light in the sky which was flashing.  it was brighter than any star and flashing, but not moving.  after about 3 nights of seeing this in the same place, we decided to observe with our telescope.  object is round, surrounded by bright lights.  the lights seem to be in rows, lining the outer edges of the object. the lights change color - white, red, yellow, blue and green.  the object moves, rotating on it's axis. it appears at approximately the same time each night.  we first see in the upper left line of sight, and it slowly moves in a diagonal track to the lower right line of sight, until we cannot see it anymore due to tree line. it takes about 30 minutes until we can no longer see it. there has been an increased amount of airplanes and helicopters flying by during these sightings.  we don't usually see this many airplanes fly by.
we have attached a 35mm digital camera to our telescope and have been able to take pictures as well as video.
content.summary: Seen nightly for the last 5 weeks, same time & location.  bright flashing lights to naked eye. circular craft through telescope

content.detailedDescription: Two brothers,johnny and bobby and i were night hunting from a vehicle when the driver,johnny noticed a light in the sky.He stopped the car and we all got out.One star came from the west,one from the east and one from the north.They slowed as they approached each other then hovered.It was a clear and fogless night.It was like looking at 3 north stars as they were brighter than the rest.They were way up there and hovered in a triangle formation.I don't remember how long they hovered but it seemed a long time.Finally,they travelled back in the direction they came from and out of sight in about 15 seconds.Sunset is a small community with hardly any exterior lighting so seeing all the stars was definitely not a problem.I don't know why i waited so long to share this.Probably because back in 1973 in rural la there wasn't anyone to.My friends mother didn't believe us the next day,plus we were night hunting.My friends are still alive and we talked about it last year.They seemed like was just any other experience.
content.summary: Saw 3 moving starlike travel 2 each other,hover,then return in direction they came from
